HEADWORD: Sea peach
<hw>Sea" peach`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A beautiful
American ascidian (<spn>Cynthia pyriformis</spn> syn. <spn>Halocynthia
pyriformis</spn>) having the size, form, velvety surface, and color of a
ripe peach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

